            . On the 24th of June I was walking with a friend in <placeName id="t18310630-126-crimeloc679">Great George-street. Westminster</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-126-crimeloc679" type="placeName" value="Great George-street. Westminster"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-126-crimeloc679" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-126-off677 t18310630-126-crimeloc679"></join> - we got clear of the gate going into the Park, when a Policeman touched my friend and asked if he had lost any thing; he said he had not, but I put my hand to my pocket, and my handkerchief was gone - the Policemen then went after the prisoners, who were walking down the street; my friend and I walked after them, and I saw this handkerchief come down Harris's trousers - they were fifty or sixty yards off when I first saw them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-126-person959">
                  DANIEL 
                  BUCKLEY
               <interp inst="t18310630-126-person959" type="surname" value="BUCKLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-126-person959" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-126-person959" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I saw the two prisoners in company, between eleven and twelve o'clock - a boy came and told me they were trying this gentleman's pockets; when they saw me they walked on quite smart - I spoke to the prosecutor; I told them to follow me, and I took the two prisoners - I saw the handkerchief come down Harris's trousers; this was between eleven and twelve o'clock.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Harris' Defence. I picked up that handkerchief round the corner - Mills was not in company with me.</p>
